1.-THE Galahads" comedy folk
singers, return to Arizona for a
limited engagement at Legend
City amusement park.


The five-man act will appear
nightly, except Monday, at Legend
City's Golden Palace saloon. The
five Valley boys who make up the
act are Comic Jack Poe, Bramlet,
George Cox, Bill Nelson and Tom
Scotch.


In addition to recent nightclub
engagements. they have just COM
pleted national tour with Jack
Linkletter' Hootenanny Show,
playing to Runaway crowds in
New Orleans, Dallas, Reno, Las
Vegas and Hollywood.

Whitney M. Young, Jr., became
Executive Director of the Ma
tional Urban League on Octo-
Der l, 1861. He was formerly
Dean of the Atlanta University
School of Social Work 1854
1861.


He did his undergraduate work
at Kentucky State College; his
graduate work at Massachusetts
Institute of Technology and the
University of MINES ota, at which
latter institution he received his
Masters Degree in social work
in 1o47. During the academic
year lo60-6l he was visiting
scholar at Harvard under a spe-
cial Rockefeller grant.


For three years he has Indus
trial Relations Secretary of the
St. Paul Urban League and from
1850 to 1854 was Executive Sec
rotary of the Omaha Urban
League. He has also been on the
faculty of St. Catherine S College
in St. Paul, the School of Social
Work of the University of Ne
braska and Creighton University
at Omaha.

A Women Auxiliary of the | C.
Homes Unit of the Boys Clubs
of Phoenix was recently organ
lied. Don Will, unit director, ex-
planned to the ladies the func-
lions of Women's Auxiliary and
the benefit they can be to the Boys
Club.


Officers we're elected; Mrs.
Sadie Harvey. President; Mrs.
Sessions, Secretary: Mrs. Erris
Harvey, Treasurer. The group
will meet the third Wednesday of
each month.

Auxiliary Formed
At Homes Boys Club
